tate control, media influence, fashion, and changing gender roles, she argues that the athletic female form helped to create a new ideal of modern womanhood in China at a time when women's emancipation and national needs went hand in hand. This book brings vividly to life the histories of these athletes and demonstrates how intertwined they were with the aims of the state and the needs of society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBody image in womenzChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMass media and sportszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aSports in popular culturezChinay20th century. 0aSportsxPolitical aspectszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aSportsxSocial aspectszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomen athleteszChinavBiography. 0aWomen in popular culturezChinay20th century. 0aWomenzChinaxSocial conditions. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482483540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774824835423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774824835/original  a978-3-11-127412-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-127715-8  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles